book_clubs.title: The Baby-sitters Club: Kristy's Great Idea
book_clubs.author: Raina Telgemeier
book_clubs.desc: Kristy, Mary Anne, Claudia, and Stacey are best friends and founding members of The Baby-sitters Club. Whatever comes up -- cranky toddlers, huge dogs, scary neighbors, prank calls -- you can count on them to save the day. Baby-sitting isn't always easy, and neither is dealing with strict parents, new families, fashion emergencies, and mysterious secrets. But no matter what, the BSC have what they need most: friendship.

book_clubs.title: Stella Diaz Has Something To Say
book_clubs.author: Angela Dominguez
book_clubs.desc: Third-grader Stella is shy and sometimes stumbles over English words...yet also feels uncertain about her Spanish around her Mexican relatives. But family and friends help Stella, and by the end of the year, she feels much more confident about sharing what she has to say.
